Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in The Gambia. The Gambian authorities have introduced measures to limit the spread of the virus.
The Government of the Gambia has set up a help line “1025” for anyone with information or concerns about coronavirus (COVID-19).
The Government of The Gambia has announced that all schools and universities will close from 18 March for 21 days and public gatherings including open markets will be suspended for 21 days. All travellers arriving from ‘hotspot’ countries, including the United Kingdom, will be isolated for 14 days upon arrival.
Additional surveillance and detection mechanisms have been put in place at Banjul International Airport and various points of entry along The Gambia’s border.
You should comply with any additional screening measures put in place by the authorities.
A number of airlines operating into Banjul International Airport are suspending operations Keep up to date with real-time information from your airline or accommodation provider on the impact on any existing travel plans.
